President Barack Obama has announced his intent to appoint and designate several individuals to key administration posts. Rhoda Mae Kerr, the Fire Chief of the Austin, Texas Fire Department, will be appointed as a member of the National Infrastructure Advisory Council. Carl Newman, CEO of the Jackson Municipal Airport Authority in Mississippi, will also be appointed as a member of the National Infrastructure Advisory Council. Ellen Ochoa, Director of the NASA Lyndon B. Johnson Space Center, will be appointed as a member of the National Science Board, National Science Foundation. Walter Ray Allen Jr., a retired professional basketball player, will be appointed as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Deborah A. Oppenheimer, an independent film producer, will also be appointed as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Scott Straus, Associate Chair and Director of Graduate Studies of Political Science at the University of Wisconsin, Madison, and Jeremy M. Weinstein, Professor of Political Science at Stanford University, will both be appointed as members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Additionally, Bridget Altenburg, Chief Operating Officer of the National Able Network, will be designated as a member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Military Academy. Brenda S. “Sue” Fulton, Director for Disruptive Channels at Pfizer Consumer Health, will also be designated as a member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Military Academy. Soudarak “Sue” Hoppin, President of the National Military Spouse Network, will be designated as a member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Air Force Academy.